			</li>
			<li>
			<p>
 converse: if <m>x^2 &lt; 9</m> then <m>x &lt; 3</m>.  This is <em> true</em> because the first statement forces <m>-3 \leq x \leq 3</m>.
			</p>
			</li>
			<li>
			<p>
 inverse: if  <m>x \geq 3</m> then <m>x^2 \geq 9</m> .  This is <em> true</em>.
			</p>
			</li>
		</ul>
</p>
